<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOMALIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Regarding the article by A.J. Bacevich (Commentary, April 1), I would like 
to ask him a question. 
</P>
<P>
 It is a concern, of course, to all of us in our country that our military in 
Somalia fired on and killed a pregnant woman and 12 other civilians, as stated 
in his article.Bacevich implies that we should not expose our military to 
situations where these unfortunate isolated incidents can happen. 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps he would prefer that we had not gone to Somalia and had let the local 
military continue its wholesale slaughter and let the starvation go on and on. 
This seems to be the conclusion from his article. I believe we took the right 
action, although maybe we pulled out too soon. 
</P>
<P>
 IRVIN C. CHAPMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 
</P>
