<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; WASHINGTON, D.C.; FARRAKHAN'S EX-AIDE AT HOLOCAUST MUSEUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Khalid Abdul Muhammad, the former top aide to Nation of Islam leader Louis 
Farrakhan who has been denounced for expressing anti-Semitic views, toured the 
Holocaust Museum and emerged contending that the genocide experienced by blacks 
has been far worse than what happened to Jews. After his 90-minute visit, 
Muhammad told reporters that the suffering inflicted by Nazis on "so-called" 
Jews and other minorities was minuscule compared with the pain that blacks have 
endured from whites for centuries. 
</P>
