ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ALISO VIEJO; WORKSHOPS TO FOCUS ON PARKS, RECREATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A series of workshops to shape the future of the community's parks and 
recreation begins April 26 at Aliso Viejo Middle School. 
</P>
<P>
 Run by the Aliso Viejo Community Assn., the first session will focus on the 
community's master plan process and other local issues. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshop will be at 7 p.m. in the multipurpose room at the middle school, 
111 Park Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Topics will include development of open space, hiking trails, sports and park 
facilities, construction of a library and a town center. 
</P>
<P>
 From Saturday to April 30, a random telephone survey will be conducted in 
Aliso Viejo between 7 and 9 p.m. to gather information about parks and 
recreation issues. 
</P>
<P>
 The workshops will be run by RJM Design Group Inc., a consultant hired by the 
Aliso Viejo Community Assn. to help draft the community parks and recreation 
master plan. 
</P>
<P>
 The sessions will take place at the middle school. Future dates are May 11, 
May 15, June 4 and July 18. 
</P>
<P>
 The meetings will start at 7 p.m., except for the June 4 workshop, which will 
start at 10 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Citizens planning to attend are asked to call association officials in advance 
at (714) 362-5890. FRANK MESSINA 
