<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: ACTIVITIES PLANNED TO HONOR THE PLANET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KAY SAILLANT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Numerous activities are being planned around the county in conjunction with 
Earth Day, which this year falls on Saturday. Among them: 
</P>
<P>
 * The Channel Islands District Garden Club will sponsor a talk on falconry at 
the Taft Ranch in Ojai on Friday.Walking tours of the ranch will be offered 
during the event, scheduled to begin at 10 a.m. Participants should bring a 
sack lunch, comfortable shoes and insect spray. Coffee and iced tea will be 
provided. A $10 donation is requested. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call Patricia Harris at 386-3356. 
</P>
<P>
 * Oxnard College will exhibit environmental-themed art and booths explaining 
products at a daylong festival scheduled to begin at 10 a.m. Saturday. 
Entertainment by ethnic dancers and other groups will be offered, along with 
short lectures on environmental themes and tours of the community college 
campus. The event will last until 4 p.m. at the college, 4000 S. Rose Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call Ron Jackson at 986-5847. 
</P>
<P>
 * Channel Islands National Park will hold a March for Park fund-raiser 
starting at 8 a.m. Saturday. People are urged to bike, walk or jog to raise 
money for a native plant garden at the national park's visitors center at 
Ventura Harbor. Organizers hope to raise $1,000 for the garden and other 
projects. The march is sponsored by Friends of Channel Islands National Park, a 
nonprofit group affiliated with the five-island park chain. 
