<HEADLINE>
<P>
LANDFILL THREAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I would like to suggest that all those hysterical souls, who by rumor and 
innuendo are whipping themselves and the Ojai Valley into a fear-driven frenzy 
over the weather radar tower on Sulphur Mountain, direct their considerable 
energies toward battling a true and distinct danger that may again be 
threatening our relatively pristine valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Over the Easter holiday, the Weldon Canyon landfill rose from the dead to 
bedevil us once again.According to The Times, Taconic Resources of San Diego 
County plans to put a countywide initiative on the November ballot authorizing 
construction of the landfill. To get the initiative on the ballot, Taconic 
Resources must collect 18,000 valid signatures by June 8. 
</P>
<P>
 With 98.5% of potential voters living outside Ojai, we can expect little help 
and / or sympathy from other sections of the county, where residents see little 
to be lost by authorizing the dumping of their trash in our airshed. In truth, 
with more than a little justification, many in the county consider us elitists 
unwilling to share in the problems that confound the entire county. 
</P>
<P>
 The loud protests of those opposed to the weather radar installation do little 
to gain the support of the voters we will need to counter the rebirth of Weldon 
Canyon -- a true and proven threat to life in the Ojai Valley as we know it. 
</P>
<P>
 CLARK B. GATHERCOLE 
</P>
<P>
 Ojai 
</P>
