<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE ARREST 6 ON DRUG CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oxnard police arrested a 60-year-old Oxnard man on drug charges and five 
alleged accomplices after completing a six-month investigation of a large 
cocaine trafficking organization, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Raymond Lopez was arrested in South Gate on Saturday afternoon after he tried 
to sell a kilogram of cocaine to undercover detectives, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 During the investigation, search warrants were served at Lopez's house on J 
Street, as well as on houses in the cities of South Gate and Bellflower. 
Investigators said they found $438,000 in cash at a Bellflower residence, and 
seized three vehicles, six handguns, three assault rifles and a sawed-off 
shotgun. 
</P>
<P>
 The other suspected drug traffickers arrested were Marino Cavada, 47, and Ives 
Enciso-Arellano, 25, both of South Gate; Hector Cabrerra, 39, of Los Angeles, 
and Jesus Padilla, 39, and Nohemi Zazueta, 25, both of Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
 All were being held at Los Angeles County Jail, police said. PEGGY Y. LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
