<P>
2 U.N. PEACEKEEPERS DIE IN SOMALIA CLASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two U.N. peacekeepers and a refugee official were killed Monday in ethnic 
fighting in Somalia. 
</P>
<P>
 The two Nepalese U.N. soldiers were killed in cross-fire between clan militias 
in Mogadishu, U.N. spokesman Maj. Chris Budge said. The refugee official, a 
Gambian, was shot by militiamen as his plane touched down in the southern town 
of Afmadu. 
</P>
