<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHIITE MILITIA LEADER KILLED BY CAR BOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A car bomb killed the military commander of the Shiite Muslim Amal movement 
Monday, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Nimeh Haidar, 34, died in an explosion when he turned the key in the ignition 
of his car to go to work near this southern Lebanese market town, according to 
police. 
</P>
