<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; MTA BUSES 
EXAMINED IN HIT-RUN INVESTIGATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Investigators examined more than half a dozen MTA buses Monday in an attempt 
to determine if any was involved in a fatal crash involving a bicyclist.  
</P>
<P>
 "It's a hit-and-run investigation.The driver and the bus have not been 
identified," said Detective Mike Fischer of the Los Angeles Police Department's 
West Traffic Division.  
</P>
<P>
 Bicyclist Otto Poggio, 31, died at the scene of the 6:53 a.m. accident at 
Santa Monica Boulevard and Gower Street, Fischer said.  
</P>
<P>
 Poggio and the bus were both eastbound, Fischer said, and as the bus passed it 
collided with the bike. 
</P>
<P>
 Poggio "lost control and went down in the roadway, at which time there was a 
second contact," Fischer said. "The bus continued eastbound. It didn't stop." 
</P>
<P>
 It was unclear if the bus actually rolled over the man, Fischer said.  
</P>
<P>
 None of the drivers admitted knowing about the accident, Fischer said, and 
"there's no indication of which bus it is." 
</P>
</TEXT>
