<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; UCI ASIAN GROUPS HOST HERITAGE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AILEEN CHO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine's Asian/Pacific Student Assn. is celebrating Asian Heritage Week 
through Thursday with various events at the student center. 
</P>
<P>
 The 9-year-old festival's theme this year is "Tying the Cultural Ribbon."The 
festival will focus on bringing together UCI's 15 Asian American cultural 
groups, said student association President Eileen Chun. The festival features 
food booths and exhibits as well as performances. 
</P>
<P>
 Peter Bacho, author of the novel "Cebu," will speak at 7:30 tonight in Crystal 
Cove Auditorium. Admission is $5. Performances by the Cambodian Student 
Organization and Chinese Assn. will be held in front of the student center from 
11 a.m. to 1:15 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 On Wednesday, "The Joy Luck Club" will be shown in the student center TV 
lounge at 7:30 p.m., and the Iranian Culture Club will perform music outside 
the center at 11 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 On Thursday, the Filipino Club, Indian Sub-Continental Club and Phi Zeta Tau 
will perform dances and skits beginning at 11 a.m. outside the student center. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 725-2000.AILEEN CHO 
</P>
</TEXT>
