<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; ACTING SECRETARY OF STATE TO GIVE TALK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California's acting Secretary of State Tony Miller will speak at Rancho 
Santiago College on Monday to emphasize the importance of voting. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller, whose office oversees elections and voter registration statewide, will 
speak with students, many of whom are in the 18- to 25-year-old age group that 
statistics show are the least likely to vote. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller will make his remarks at 11:30 a.m. in the quad area of the Santa Ana 
campus, said Rancho spokesman Dale Ruhe. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, at 11:15 a.m. Miller will meet informally with students in the Board of 
Trustees meeting room, on the second floor of the administration building, Ruhe 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is free and open to the public. The campus is at 17th and Bristol 
streets. For more information, call (714) 564-6452.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
