<P>
NAZI LEADER PORTRAIT TO STAY IN NEBRASKA SCHOOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A portrait of Nazi leader Heinrich Himmler that provoked a free-speech 
controversy at tiny Midland Lutheran College will continue to hang in the 
college library, the school's president said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 A faculty committee agreed with a student group that the life-size painting, 
which has hung in the library for 10 years, should be accompanied by an 
