<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 4 NAMED TO AGENCY FOR DISABLED RIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson has named four people to the Area XI Board of Developmental 
Disabilities, a state advocate agency designed to protect the rights of the 
disabled, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The five-member board is responsible for promoting public and professional 
awareness of barriers to the developmentally disabled throughout the county. 
</P>
<P>
 Appointees include Tou Yer Moua, 30, of Santa Ana; Christopher P. Hill, 42, of 
Santa Ana; Omadell Johnson, 73, of Orange, and Joyce C. Wing, 62, of Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 Moua and Johnson will serve one-year terms. Wing and Hill will serve for two 
years.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
