<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; TRUCK DRIVER DIES IN FREEWAY CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 40-year-old Pico Rivera man was killed Monday when his tractor-trailer 
struck a center divider on the Orange Freeway, then veered back across the road 
and crashed into a sound wall, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, identified as Angel Miguel Martin, was pronounced dead at the 
scene. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the California Highway Patrol, the left front tire of Martin's 
truck blew, causing him to lose control. 
</P>
<P>
 "It appears that he was killed, or at least knocked unconscious, (by) the 
first impact," said CHP Officer Angel Johnson, "and the truck drifted across 
the road." 
</P>
<P>
 The crash took place in the freeway's southbound lanes at Orangethorpe Road at 
11:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 A small diesel spill from the big rig's fuel tanks slowed southbound traffic 
for several hours, Johnson said. MARK I. PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
