<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; CITY TO CO-SPONSOR FUND-RAISING EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has agreed to co-sponsor a carnival next month at the Seal Beach 
Naval Weapons Station despite opposition from a few residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The annual event is being organized by the Seal Beach Chamber of Commerce to 
help nonprofit groups raise money.The groups can run merchandise booths at the 
carnival, which will include food vendors and 30 amusement park rides. 
</P>
<P>
 Two residents at Monday's council said the city should not be involved in the 
fund-raising event. One of the residents questioned whether all the 
organizations that take part in the carnival are properly registered with the 
state as nonprofit groups. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager Jerry L. Bankston said the organizations must have state licenses 
in order to receive booths. He said many of the groups -- which include the 
local animal shelter and PTA -- have previously sought financial assistance 
from city. But the city has been unable to fund the groups because of its tight 
budget. 
</P>
<P>
 Seal Beach will spend no money organizing the May 12-15 event. The city will 
provide security, but the chamber has agreed to reimburse Seal Beach for all 
costs.SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</TEXT>
