ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; MAN DIES IN HEAD-ON CRASH ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 23-year-old Santa Ana man was killed early Monday in a head-on collision 
when he drove the wrong way on the Riverside Freeway, the California Highway 
Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers said they believe Guadalupe Medina Albarran was under the influence 
of alcohol when his pickup collided head-on with a station wagon just west of 
Coal Canyon Road in Anaheim Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was partially ejected from the pickup and was pronounced dead at the 
scene, according to Officer Robert Polzin. 
</P>
<P>
 Three occupants of the station wagon, the 19-year-old driver, a 35-year-old 
woman and a 15-year-old girl, all from Moreno Valley, sustained moderate 
injuries, and were taken to Kaiser Permanente-Anaheim Medical Center. 
</P>
