<TEXT>
<P>
 Gail Wickstrom, superintendent of the Westminster School District, will slip 
on her tap-dancing shoes and perform a number or two during an April 28 variety 
show to raise money for school supplies. 
</P>
<P>
 Wickstrom is one of about 40 teachers, administrators and staff who will 
perform in the second annual variety show staged by the district's Foundation 
for Educational Excellence, district spokeswoman Audrey Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit group, which was formed in 1990, supports student programs and 
raises money for district projects. The foundation has awarded more than 
$10,000 in mini-grants to local teachers, funded student field trips and 
anti-drug programs, and honored more than 2,000 students during awards 
presentations, Brown said. 
</P>
