<P>
TWO CRITICALLY HURT IN SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two people were shot and critically wounded while riding in a car in the 
vicinity of 5th and Euclid streets late Monday night, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the victims, an unidentified woman, was shot in the head, said Police 
Sgt. Anthony Levatino. An unidentified man was shot in the back, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Two other people in the car were not hurt, Levatino said. Their names were 
also unavailable. 
</P>
<P>
 Details of the attack, which occurred about 10:10 p.m., were unavailable 
Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The two victims were taken to Fountain Valley Regional Hospital and Medical 
Center, where they were listed in critical condition, Levatino said. 
</P>
