<P>
WEEKEND BOX OFFICE; HEY, CHEVY, THE BRITISH ARE COMING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TERRY PRISTIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An independent British comedy that has been gradually adding theaters 
unceremoniously pushed aside a new suitor starring Chevy Chase and Jack Palance 
to lead the box-office procession. But, overall, filing tax returns apparently 
did not put the public in a film-going mood, and attendance dipped to its 
lowest point in nearly a year.Other new entries, including "White Fang 2," the 
sequel to a popular 1991 film, also failed to catch on. 
</P>
