<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: SUPERIOR INDUSTRIES REPORTS RECORD 1ST-QUARTER PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Superior Industries International Inc., a Van Nuys-based supplier of cast 
aluminum wheels, reported a record profit and record revenues for its first 
quarter that ended March 31. 
</P>
<P>
 The company's profit was $12.5 million, up 24% from $10.1 million in the same 
period last year. Revenue in the latest quarter rose to $105.9 million, up 8% 
compared with $98.1 million in the same period a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the gain to growth in sales of aluminum wheels to Ford 
and General Motors. 
</P>
