<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: DOLE'S 1ST-QUARTER NET DROPS 44% TO $29.7 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dole Food Co., a Westlake Village food and real estate concern, reported that 
its first-quarter net income dropped 44% from a year-earlier period. 
</P>
<P>
 In the three months ended March 26, Dole earned $29.7 million, in contrast 
with a $53.3-million profit in the first quarter of 1993. But a year earlier it 
had a $30.9-million one-time gain from its real estate subsidiary's stock sale. 
Its revenue in the latest quarter rose 7%, to $818.8 million from $766.5 
million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company said that the market for bananas, one of its biggest products, 
improved in the first quarter as it continued to reduce its costs, but lower 
prices for lettuce, celery and canned pineapple and concentrate reduced its 
overall results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
