<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: WITH DESIGN IN MIND REPORTS $1.17-MILLION LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With Design In Mind International Inc., a Woodland Hills marketer of toys, 
reported a loss of $1.17 million for the three months that ended Dec. 31 on 
sales of $1.08 million. 
</P>
<P>
 In the same quarter a year earlier, the company had a loss of $406,761 on 
sales of $478,702.With Design In Mind has been restructuring since late 1992, 
and last year changed its fiscal year so that it ends Dec. 31, instead of Sept. 
30. 
</P>
<P>
 For all of 1993, the company posted a loss of $2.92 million on sales of $1.56 
million. For its fiscal year that ended in September, 1992, With Design In Mind 
lost $4.61 million on sales of $3.63 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The company recently relocated its general offices to Woodland Hills from 
Chatsworth to reduce costs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
