<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: XIRCOM REPORTS RECORD PROFITS IN 2ND QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Xircom Inc., a Calabasas maker of equipment for portable personal computers, 
said it had record profits and revenues for its fiscal second quarter and for 
the six months that ended March 31. 
</P>
<P>
 The company reported a second-quarter profit of $3.9 million, up 84% from $2.1 
million in the second quarter last year.Revenue in the fiscal second quarter 
rose to $30.2 million, up 62% compared with $18.7 million in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months, the company reported a profit of $7.35 million, up 88% 
from $3.92 million in the same period last year. The profit surge was from 
revenues of $56.6 million, up 58% from $35.9 million a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
 Xircom attributed its results to increased sales of its external adapters for 
personal computers and the introduction in the second quarter of a new product, 
a combination modem and adapter contained on a credit card. 
</P>
</TEXT>
