REGIONAL EARNINGS: VITESSE SEMICONDUCTOR REPORTS LOWER LOSSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vitesse Semiconductor Corp., a Camarillo maker of gallium arsenide computer 
chips, said it narrowed its fiscal second-quarter loss to $1.7 million, from a 
loss of $5.1 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For the quarter that ended March 31, the company said revenue surged 44%, to 
$8.72 million from $6.07 million a year earlier. The company attributed the 
improved results to increased shipments to the communications market and cost 
reduction. 
</P>
<P>
 For the six months that ended March 31, Vitesse pared its loss to $4.4 
million, from a loss of $11.6 million a year earlier. Sales for the latest 
six-month period grew 47%, to $16.8 million from $11.4 million a year earlier. 
</P>
