<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: LAKE VIEW TERRACE; POLICE IDENTIFY MAN SLAIN NEAR DAM PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities on Monday identified a San Fernando man as the motorist who was 
fatally shot during a car chase this weekend near Hansen Dam Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Louie Herrera, 23, died after a bullet struck him in the back of the head 
Sunday as he was driving eastbound on Foothill Boulevard near Osborne Street, 
Los Angeles Police Lt. Gary Hallden said. 
</P>
<P>
 Homicide detectives are searching for two males in a light blue Nissan pickup 
truck who fired several shots at Herrera as they drove behind his El Camino, 
Hallden said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that the pickup positioned itself behind and to the 
right of Herrera's car before the truck's passenger leaned out a window and 
fired seven times, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 After he was shot, Herrera lost control of his car, which rolled over once 
before hitting several parked cars, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Paramedics pronounced Herrera dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Originally, investigators believed the shooting stemmed from either a gang 
dispute or an argument in the park. But on Monday, police discounted both 
possibilities. 
</P>
<P>
 "We do not know what happened," said Hallden. "But as far as we know, it had 
nothing to do with (a confrontation) in the park or was gang-related. . . . We 
do know the vehicles had probably been following each other a long time before 
the shooting." TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</TEXT>
