<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; MISSOURI; APARTMENT OWNERS FACE BIAS CHARGES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three St. Louis-area apartment complexes have been charged by the Justice 
Department for alleged discrimination against African American renters.The 
suits charge that apartment owners and managers, all in a largely white section 
of St. Louis, "routinely refused to show units to black prospective tenants 
claiming they were unavailable." Meanwhile, whites were told the units were 
available. The apartment complexes face a civil penalty of up to $50,000 for 
the first violation and $100,000 for subsequent violations. About 15 cases were 
recently filed in five states as part of a 17-month nationwide investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
