<HEADLINE>
<P>
CYPRESS WINS, DROPS FULLERTON OUT OF FIRST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jenny Lopez pitched a four-hitter as host Cypress won its seventh consecutive 
Orange Empire Conference softball game Monday with a 2-1 victory over 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The loss dropped Fullerton (21-14, 11-4) out of first place for the first time 
this season. Orange Coast, which beat Riverside, 3-1, Monday, has a one-game 
lead over the Hornets. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez (14-8), who walked seven, was far from solid. Cypress (34-14, 10-5 in 
conference) also made four errors. Fullerton left 13 runners on. 
</P>
<P>
 Alison Murphy scored on a two-out error in the fourth to break a 1-1 tie. 
</P>
</TEXT>
