<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY DIGEST: TATE SIGNS LETTER OF INTENT WITH IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura College basketball player Michael Tate, who helped lead the Pirates to 
the junior college state championship game, signed a letter of intent Monday to 
play for UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Tate, a 6-5 sophomore, averaged 13 points and 9.1 rebounds a game for Ventura, 
and was named to the All-Western State Conference team and the state 
championship all-tournament team. 
</P>
<P>
 Tate also considered Utah, San Diego State, Utah State and Pacific. Softball 
</P>
<P>
 Notre Dame High pitcher Crista Corpening signed a letter of intent to play 
softball for Boston College. 
</P>
<P>
 Corpening (4-6), a right-hander, also considered San Diego State and UC Davis. 
Regional Results 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe 11, North Hollywood 2 -- Viking ace Joel Zamudio returned from a 13-day 
absence and pitched five hitless innings for Monroe (4-8, 3-4) in a Valley 
Pac-8 Conference game. Zamudio, who experienced soreness in his right shoulder 
nearly two weeks ago, was replaced after throwing his limit of 75 pitches. 
</P>
<P>
 Sylmar 8, Van Nuys 0 -- The Spartans (16-3, 7-0) parlayed six hits and two 
errors into a seven-run sixth inning in a Valley Pac-8 game at Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Velazco (7-1), who had a run-scoring double in the sixth, pitched a 
three-hitter and struck out seven. 
</P>
<P>
 Poly 5, Canoga Park 0 -- Senior right-hander Jerry Delgado did not give up a 
hit through 6 1/3 innings before surrendering a single to Javier Vasquez in a 
Valley Pac-8 game at Poly. 
</P>
<P>
 Delgado (4-0) finished with a one-hitter. He walked one and struck out one. 
Jaime Cerna went three for three and drove in a run for Poly (14-2, 6-1). Sam 
Vizcarra hit two doubles and Gowdy Martinez went two for three. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant 6, Birmingham 4 -- Marc Scorza's two-run triple keyed a four-run first 
inning and Grant (8-5, 5-2) held on to beat Birmingham (6-11, 2-5) in a Valley 
Pac-8 game. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 8, Agoura 3 -- Jeff Bennett and Rich Adams each homered and drove 
in three runs to lead the Panthers (13-4, 6-0) in a Marmonte League game at 
Newbury Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Royal 4, Thousand Oaks 2 -- Benny Lemos drove in three runs, including the 
go-ahead score in the sixth inning, in a Marmonte League game at Royal. 
</P>
<P>
 Maki Kramer (7-0) pitched a three-hitter. He allowed one earned run and struck 
out seven for Royal (11-5, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake 10, Channel Islands 7 -- Dave Bartlestone had two hits and drove in 
two runs for Westlake (11-7, 2-3) in a Marmonte League game at Channel Islands. 
</P>
